DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T110000
DTSTAMP:20260402T221024
CREATED:20260326T194344Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260326T194459Z
UID:10030966-1775296800-1775300400@www.phinneycenter.org
SUMMARY:Phinney Neighbors Organize: neighborhood preparedness orientation
DESCRIPTION:Room 6\, Blue Building \nResilient neighborhoods start with strong connections. When we work together\, we’re better prepared to bounce back from any disaster. Whether you live in a house\, apartment\, or condo\, learn how to team up with your neighbors to stay safe. \nPhinney Hub makes it easy (and fun!) to get your block organized. We provide the tools and support you need to turn preparedness into a great way to meet neighbors. Come see how simple it is to build a safer\, more connected community together. \nPresented by Phinney Emergency Hub \nQuestions? Please email: PhinneyHub@gmail.com \n  \n 
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/phinney-neighbors-organize-neighborhood-preparedness-orientation/
LOCATION:Phinney Center Campus: Blue (upper) Building\, 6532 Phinney Ave. N.\, Seattle\, WA\, 98103\, United States
CATEGORIES:Renter Event
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/webp:https://media.phinneycenter.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/15135237/Team-Picture.webp
ORGANIZER;CN="Phinney Emergency Hub":MAILTO:phinneyhub@gmail.com
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260405T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260405T213000
DTSTAMP:20260402T221024
CREATED:20260312T202142Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260312T202142Z
UID:10030956-1775415600-1775424600@www.phinneycenter.org
SUMMARY:Medusa Quartet - genre-defying chamber-folk ensemble
DESCRIPTION:Named after one of mythology’s most misunderstood figures\, the Medusa Quartet channels the power of transformation\, reclaiming what was once feared and turning it into something fiercely magical. Saskia Tomkins – Violin\, Viola\, Cello\, Nyckelharpa; Marta Solek – Suka\, Plock Fiddle\, Cello; Lea Kirstein – Violin\, Viola\, Cello; Georgia Hathaway – Violin\, Vocals – A genre-defying chamber-folk quartet that fuses centuries-old string traditions with contemporary storytelling and original compositions.  Medusa’s dynamic arrangement style cross-pollinates the sounds of Middle Eastern\, Scandinavian\, Celtic\, Appalachian\, and Eastern European music\, as well as original tunes\, to create something previously unheard. The dynamic band connects audiences across dividing lines of culture and identity to reveal the common threads beneath. Join us for a very special concert! \nDoors open at 6:30 pm for the 7:00 pm concert in the Phinney Center’s Community Hall (lower Brick Building). \nTickets are available in advance online\, in-person at prior SFS concerts\, or at the door.
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/medusa-quartet-genre-defying-chamber-folk-ensemble/
LOCATION:Phinney Center Campus: Brick (lower) Building\, 6532 Phinney Ave. N.\, Seattle\, 98103\, United States
CATEGORIES:Renter Event
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://media.phinneycenter.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/12130211/Medusa_goldlines.jpeg
ORGANIZER;CN="Seattle Folklore Society Concerts":MAILTO:concerts@seafolklore.org
END:VEVENT
